\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {1}{\ignorespaces Memory poisoning threat model. The adversary injects adversarial entries $p_{\mathrm  {adv}}$ into the memory store $\mathcal  {M}$. When a victim query $q$ is issued, the poisoned entry is retrieved as top-$k$ context, causing the agent to produce an attacker-controlled response. The three attacks differ in how $p_{\mathrm  {adv}}$ is crafted and how write access to $\mathcal  {M}$ is obtained.}}{4}{figure.caption.8}\protected@file@percent }
